metadata.name: Geoetris #48
metadata.description:
In 'Geoetris', the random mixture of simple geometric forms and vibrant colour palettes converge towards an artistic manifestation of geometric abstraction.


The collection is limited to 161 works of art, the first three digits of the golden ratio, a number often encountered when taking the ratios of distances in geometric figures.

-----

Press 's' to save a high resolution PNG at 10000 x 10000 px.
Press 'e' to save the current canvas view.

-----

Features:

Palette: dark1, dark2, dark3, vrolik1, vrolik2, retro1, retro2, origami, magma, jungle, lava, tuscany
Background: derived from the palette
Partitions: partitions,
Noisy: true, false


-----

Artwork by @cristianrohr.

Made with P5js and <3.

metadata.name: fx(splash) #218
metadata.description:
To celebrate fx(hash) turning 1 year old I've created this token as a part of the #fxhashturnsone event! It's a playful and colorful token symbolizing the experiences I've had with this platform.


The piece uses shaders to generate it's visuals which means that outputs will vary from device to device, and the preview might not look the exact same as your live view.

For that same reason I do not recommend running this piece on a mobile device as the shaders can be quite heavy and blurry on lower-tier hardware. My recommended way of viewing this token is on a pc.


--

To open the export menu double click the screen. Here you can export in a multitude of resolutions.

--


50% of primary proceeds will be donated to the processing foundation, learn more about them here:
https://processingfoundation.org

Made with opengl shaders and p5js by WootScoot, 2022.

metadata.name: Oxygen #59
metadata.description:
Oxygen makes strange forms of life thrive even in the darkest of places.

This is a generative piece using curated randomness to create textures, generate distortion fields, simulate growth and create compositions.

The work is best viewed in high resolution, but due to the time it takes to render, the preview image is capped to only 1000 pixels in height. You can change the resolution by pressing keys

- 'm' for medium  (height=2000px)
- 'l' for large (height=3500px)
- 'x' for extra large (height=5000px) 

outputs. 

Press 's' to save the output as a PNG file.

For even larger outputs, you can open the work in live mode and append the text '?size=10000' to the URL. Here, you can change the number (10000) to the desired height in pixels. 

Please note, that a very high-resolution image may take a very long time to render and some browsers are not able to save the image. However, even a 10000 pixels tall outputs have been generated during testing.

metadata.name: How to Draw Bubbles (◕‿◕)♡ #176
metadata.description:
[The solidness or volume of the form could be obtained by using highlights on one side of each object and shading on the opposite side.]


(⊃｡•́‿•̀｡)⊃━━━━☆

Wishing you easy, light and bubbly 2023!

metadata.name: Connect-us #147
metadata.description:
We are all connected. That's a knowledge we once knew very well, but has long been deliberately hidden from us.

Let us all remove those ugly, unjustifiable barriers that were forcefully inserted between us at a time long forgotten, by those who'll never be remembered, right here, right now.

Let us connect!

* * *

- 30% Primary & 25% Royalties will go to @Savepakistanorg

- 10% Primary will be used for minting #fxhashturnsone works of fellow artists and sent to top collectors of Misunderstanding & Connect-us, on Nov 21.

Reserved pieces are allocated to my top collectors, thank you so much for your continuous support!
